Class ScriptClientExecutionException

    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • com.vector.cfg.automation.scripting.base.ScriptingException
            • com.vector.cfg.automation.scripting.api.ScriptExecutionException
              • com.vector.cfg.automation.scripting.api.ScriptClientExecutionException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ScriptingException.IScriptingClientExecutionException, IDebugable, IExceptionAggregatesCauseChainInUserMessage, IUserMessage, java.io.Serializable

    @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
 @PublishedApiDomain(value=AUTOMATION_IF)
public class ScriptClientExecutionException
extends ScriptExecutionException
implements ScriptingException.IScriptingClientExecutionException
    The script task can throw an ScriptClientExecutionException to abort the execution of an IScriptTask, and display a meaningful message to the user.
    Reserved Return Codes
    The returns codes 0-20 are reversed for internal use of the DaVinci Configurator, and are not allowed to be used by a client script. Also negative returns codes are not permitted.

      • ScriptClientExecutionException

        @PublishedMethod
public ScriptClientExecutionException(java.lang.Integer consoleReturnCode,
                                                        java.lang.String message)
        Instantiates a new ScriptClientExecutionException.
        Exception with Console Return Code
        An ScriptClientExecutionException with an return code of type Integer will also abort the execution of the IScriptTask.

        But it also changes the return code of the console application, if the IScriptTask was executed in the console application. This could be used when the console application of the DaVinci Configurator is called for other scripts or batch files.

        Parameters:
        consoleReturnCode - the console return code
        message - the message
